<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-515] Gossiper misses first updates when restarting a node</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-515</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Easy way to reproduce:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Start node A.&lt;br/&gt;
Start node B, with autobootstrap=false.&lt;br/&gt;
Kill B, wipe data dir, and restart (still w/ autobootstrap=false).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A will show B as down, with its old token.  (B will see both nodes correctly.)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This appears to be because when you wipe data dir, generation restarts at 1.  (This is not just operator error; besides during testing, this could arise if a node dies completely and has to be replaced.)  Then gossip state is ignored until the new heartbeat is larger than the one previously reached.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It appears that initializing the generation to seconds-since-epoch would fix this.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
